      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
         <p>The papers of the George Montfort Gilchrist family span the years
		  1854-1921 and consist of correspondence, school records, literary and
		  commencement programs, poetry, and genealogical records. Much of the
		  correspondence is between Gilchrist, a captain in the Third Indiana Cavalry,
		  and his wife, Mollie Gilpin Gilchrist. Gilchrist's wartime letters describe
		  routine camp life, troop movements, and skirmishes with Confederate forces in
		  Virginia, Maryland, and Pennsylvania. Other Civil War letters are between
		  Mollie and Samuel J. V. B. Gilpin of the First Indiana Cavalry and Ebenezer N.
		  Gilpin of the Third Iowa Cavalry. In addition, there is considerable
		  correspondence with other members of the Gilchrist and Gilpin families. The
		  school records, literary programs, and commencement programs pertain to Hanover
		  College, Hanover, Indiana. The genealogical records are of the Gilpin family of
		  Illinois, Iowa, and Indiana.</p>
      </scopecontent>
